<subSubSection id="C358655E861A6B3CFDB08D8AFEBFFC5A" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861A6B3CFDB08D8AFCACFDBF" blockId="8.[616,822,510,548]" box="[616,822,510,548]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">PI. 1 fig. 4</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861A6B3CFECC8E2EFEDBFCFC" blockId="8.[225,1209,602,1887]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Description. Shell very small with rather thick, biconvex lenticular form, isostrophic and smooth with an acute keel at periphery; umbilici closed on both sides by last whorl. Aperture with a deep angular sinus culminating at the periphery in a long narrow slit; lips thick.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861A6B3CFECB8F1BFEBFFC5A" blockId="8.[225,1209,602,1887]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">
