<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861A6B3CFECB8F8DFE48FBE6" blockId="8.[225,1209,602,1887]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">
Type locality. About 
<quantity id="4CBA9B30861A6B3CFD508F8DFD75FBBA" box="[648,751,1017,1057]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" unit="m" value="250.0">250 m</quantity>
west of Babbinboon Lane, in Swains Gully, 
<quantity id="4CBA9B30861A6B3CFDFB885DFD14FBD4" box="[547,654,1065,1103]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" unit="km" value="15.0">15 km</quantity>
south-west of Somerton, NSW (Locality 25).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861A6B3CFECB88F0FC66FB42" blockId="8.[225,1209,602,1887]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">
Stratigrapbic position. In bioclastic limestone, 
<quantity id="4CBA9B30861A6B3CFBA788F0FE98FB42" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" unit="m" value="130.0">130 m</quantity>
above the base of the Namoi Formation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861A6B3CFECB8895FE48FAAD" blockId="8.[225,1209,602,1887]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">
Additional material. 
<specimenCount id="9D44FD5C861A6B3CFD778895FC10FA93" box="[687,906,1249,1288]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" type="generic">3 specimens</specimenCount>
from 'Marohn' (Locality 28).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C358655E861A6B3CFECB8949FE19FA09" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861A6B3CFECB8949FE19FA09" blockId="8.[225,1209,602,1887]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Geograpbic distribution. From Swains Gully to 'Marohn'.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C358655E861A6B3CFECB89EDFBABFA5B" box="[275,1073,1433,1472]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" type="multiple">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861A6B3CFECB89EDFBABFA5B" blockId="8.[225,1209,602,1887]" box="[275,1073,1433,1472]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Geological age. Middle to late Tournaisian.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C358655E861A6B3CFECA89BCFB2CF986" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861A6B3CFECA89BCFB2CF986" blockId="8.[225,1209,602,1887]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">
Etymology. Derived from the Latin 
<emphasis id="B936EAC7861A6B3CFC7E89BCFB88FA74" box="[934,1042,1480,1519]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">carina</emphasis>
meaning carinate; referring to the spiral ridge at the periphery.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C358655E861A6B3CFECA8A50FCFEF8C4" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861A6B3CFECA8A50FCFEF8C4" blockId="8.[225,1209,602,1887]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">
Remarks. This is a relatively rare species, and is characterised by a smooth biconvex shell with a long slit and peripheral keel. The specimens are similar to the type species 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56861A6B3CFE038ADAFC59F94E" authority="Koken" authorityName="Koken" authorityYear="1896" box="[475,963,1710,1749]" class="Gastropoda" genus="Cymbularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bellerophontida" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="galeata">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7861A6B3CFE038ADAFCA2F94E" box="[475,824,1710,1749]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Cymbularia galeata</emphasis>
Koken
</taxonomicName>
in having a smooth convolute spire with a long narrow slit, but differs in that C. 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56861A6B3CFE7B8B7DFDBAF8AB" authorityName="Koken" authorityYear="1896" box="[419,544,1801,1840]" class="Gastropoda" genus="Cymbularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bellerophontida" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="galeata">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7861A6B3CFE7B8B7DFDBAF8AB" box="[419,544,1801,1840]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">galeata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an asymmetrical adult shell and in lacking a keel on the periphery.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
